\begin_layout Standard
For those interested, here are the Fixed Point Theorems Chris mentioned
 in class:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Theorem
Brouwer's Fixed Point Theorem: Suppose that 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{A}\subset\mathbb{R}^{n}$
\end_inset

 is a nonempty compact, convex set, and that 
\begin_inset Formula $f:\mathbb{A}\rightarrow\mathbb{A}$
\end_inset

 is a continuous function from 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{A}$
\end_inset

 unto itself.
 Then 
\begin_inset Formula $f(\cdot)$
\end_inset

 has a fixed point, or there exists an 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{x}^{*}\in\mathbb{A}$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula $f(\vec{x}^{*})=\vec{x}^{*}$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Note that the key here is that the domain and the target of the function
 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 are the identical, compact, and convex; just like the strategy space of
 the aggregate best response correspondence we saw in class.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The version for correspondences, which applies to the best response graphs
 we see in this class, is:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Theorem
Kakutani's Fixed Point Theorem: Suppose that 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{A}\subset\mathbb{R}^{n}$
\end_inset

 is a nonempty compact, convex set, and that 
\begin_inset Formula $f:\mathbb{A}\rightarrow\mathbb{A}$
\end_inset

 is an upper hemi-continuous correspondence from 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{A}$
\end_inset

 into itself with the property that the set 
\begin_inset Formula $f(x)\subset\mathbb{A}$
\end_inset

 is nonempty and convex for every 
\begin_inset Formula $x\in\mathbb{A}$
\end_inset

.
 Then 
\begin_inset Formula $f(\cdot)$
\end_inset

 has a fixed point, or there exists an 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{x}^{*}\in\mathbb{A}$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula $f(\vec{x}^{*})=\vec{x}^{*}$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

